<H2>Mathematics in Industry Institute for Teachers</H2>

<H1>2005 Summer Workshop</H1>

<P>As part of the Mathematics in Industry Institute for Teachers, a summer
Workshop will be organized at WPI on July 11-15, 2005.</P>

<P>During the workshop 50 teachers will work with faculty, industrial
mathematicians and undergraduates on finding the best ways to use real-world
problems to motivate students and in particular women and underrepresented
minorities to pursue careers in mathematics, engineering, information technology
or finance/economics.</P>

<H3>Application</H3>

<P>There is no fee for the workshop. A $500 stipend is provided to the workshop
participants.</P>

<P>Here is the <A HREF="application.html">application form </A> .</P>

<H3>Housing</H3>

<P>There are two options for housing. Please indicate your choice on the
application form.</P>

<UL>
  <LI>dormitory housing at WPI (double occupancy) at <I>no charge </I>to the
    participants.<BR>
    Rooms include towels, bedding (sheets, pillows, etc.), but these rooms are
    not air-conditioned.<BR>
    <BR>
  <LI>the <A HREF="http://www.worcestercourtyard.com" TARGET="_blank">Courtyard Marriott</A>
    which is about 10-15 minutes walk to the campus (air conditioning, cable TV,
    etc.)<BR>
    <BR>
</UL>

<P>Dorm rooms are reserved in Institute Hall (building G on the
<A HREF="http://www.wpi.edu/About/Visitors/campusmap.html">campus map</A>).
On Sunday afternoon, the keys can be found at the registration desk in
Institute Hall between 3:00 p.m. and 9:00 p.m. For those arriving later,
the keys will be available at the Campus Police, located at 35 Dean Street
(building 7 on the <A HREF="http://www.wpi.edu/About/Visitors/campusmap.html">campus
map</A>).</P>

<P>For more information you can call the Mathematical Sciences Department at
(508)-831-5241 during between 7:30 am and 4:00 pm on weekdays, or the Campus Police at
(508)-831-5433.</P>

<H3>Workshop Program</H3>

<P>The draft of the workshop program is available <A
HREF="~heinrich/schedule2005.html">here</A>, or 
as an Excel file <A HREF="~heinrich/Schedule2005.xls">here.</A></P>

<P>Every day starts with continental breakfast in the Campus Center
lobby at 8:00am.  THe talks begin at 9:00am in Olin Hall (except for
Tuesday, when the talks are in Salisbury Hall).

The teams break-out sessions will be in Daniels Hall (building A on
the campus map) in the
Project-based Learning Community rooms.</P>


